# Purpose: Make the `output` field of a ResourceFunctionType optional so that
# resource functions/actions which return nothing (e.g. POST-style actions with
# no meaningful response body) can be represented. This relaxes the previous
# requirement that every resource function declare an output type, and updates
# the markdown writer to skip the "Output" bullet and its nested type traversal
# when no output is present. Enables modeling the full range of resource actions.
#
commit 6d43bf04bac42ada9c6c8208807026d7d6f20304
Author: Heng Lu <henglu@microsoft.com>
Date:   Thu Mar 23 13:57:16 2023 +0800

    support all actions

